------------------------------------------------------------------------
r137 | (no author) | 2013-12-28 20:21:46 +0530 (Sat, 28 Dec 2013) | 8 lines
Merged via: r143

** tcon, res2, and res4 modules now have a menu bar from where the hardware can be re-connected without exiting the application.

** A new class named XLIA_Driver has been implemented to make xlia module more readable.

** While plotting X-F, X-axis is changed to log scale in non-uniform frequency stepping mode.

-- Krish

------------------------------------------------------------------------
r136 | (no author) | 2013-12-28 14:32:37 +0530 (Sat, 28 Dec 2013) | 12 lines
Merged via: r143

** Susceptibility module structure has been unified with res2 and res4.

** A separate class named XLIA_Driver has been implemented in xlia module.

** Export callback implemented in AppAnalyzer module. It save the data in csv format.

** In susceptibility measurement, chi is normalized with respect to reference amplitude as well as reference frequency. This is required because secondary pickup of the susceptometer is linearly dependant on both drive amplitude and frequency.

** While plotting X-F, the user has a choice to perform either uniform stepping or non-uniform stepping. In the former, the stepping size is fixed, while in the latter the stepping size is expressed as a percentage of the current frequency. Thus while sweeping over a large range, non-uniform stepping is more useful.

-- Krish

------------------------------------------------------------------------
r135 | (no author) | 2013-12-26 16:18:53 +0530 (Thu, 26 Dec 2013) | 14 lines
Merged via: r143

** The following modules now use XFloatEntry and XIntegerEntry widgets.

	-- app_tcon, tcon
	-- app_res2, res2
	-- app_res4, res4
	-- app_xlia, xlia
	-- app_sus,  sus

** TCON_Driver has been implemented as an independant class.

** Module tcon, res2, and res4 structures have been made identical.

-- Krish

------------------------------------------------------------------------
r133 | (no author) | 2013-12-23 14:07:26 +0530 (Mon, 23 Dec 2013) | 12 lines
Merged via: r143

** Qrius has some entry widgets that change background color while typing. These are particularly important when communicating to a hardware. For example, the temperature setpoint widget becomes white while typing and becomes yellow after the entered value is successfully set.

Earlier this was done explicitely in the callback of each widget. This increases the length of the code, and makes it untidy. Three classes, viz. XEntry, XFloatEntry, and XIntegerEntry, have been implemented to incorporate this feature at the widget level.

Here, the widget changes its background color to 'peach puff' (light red) on each callback, which is initiated if the user has typed in a new value or by pressing 'Enter'.

In the callback routine, the widget value is reset to actual (e.g. the value as returned by the hardware), which also sets its background color to 'yellow'.

Currently only 'tcon' module is using this widget. All other modules need to use this.

-- Krish

------------------------------------------------------------------------
r132 | (no author) | 2013-12-23 13:48:59 +0530 (Mon, 23 Dec 2013) | 1 line
Merged via: r143

Devel branch XWidget created -- Krish
