------------------------------------------------------------------------
r122 | (no author) | 2013-12-20 15:30:17 +0530 (Fri, 20 Dec 2013) | 10 lines
Merged via: r125, r124

** A new module, named XDict, has been added. This is used to store/retrieve run data using python's dictionary object. The dictionary format has been updated to incorporate (data, unit) as a tuple against a single key. Earlier they are stored using two seperate keys. However, the old runs can still be oened using a compatibility scheme implemented in XDict.

** AppAnalyzer has been re-written using XDict and Plot2D class.

** Widget icons have been made uniform throughout the program. Now they are controlled from a single line in main.py using tkFont module.

** A number of unwanted modules have been deleted, i.e. fileio, fileie, plotxy, tlog.

-- Krish

------------------------------------------------------------------------
r121 | (no author) | 2013-12-18 20:27:50 +0530 (Wed, 18 Dec 2013) | 10 lines
Merged via: r125, r124

** Module res2 checked and heavily re-written using object oriented approach.

** Plot2D module added for generic plotting. This module supports zoom and pan while being updated in real time acquisition.

** Module plotrt, plotxt, and plote have been removed. Plot2D is being used in all places, except analyzer, which still uses plotxy.

** Module res4, tcon, and sus have been updated to incorporate Plot2D

-- Krish

------------------------------------------------------------------------
r107 | (no author) | 2013-12-14 19:40:19 +0530 (Sat, 14 Dec 2013) | 8 lines
Merged via: r125, r124, r121

** The temperature recording loop in 'tcon' module has been updated as per with acquisition loop in 'res4' module.

In the current implementation, the real time temperature data is logged in a tab seperated file, named 'last_run.log'. This file is created inside USR_DATA_FOLDER/htr directory, where USR_DATA_FOLDER is chosen by the user using 'Global Settings' menu. This file is over-written every time a new run is started. The sole purpose of this file is to provide a way to retrieve the data in case of an unwanted termination of a run, e.g. due to power failure.

On successful completion of a run, the entire data is saved using Python's dictionary format in a time stamped file inside USR_DATA_FOLDER/htr directory.

-- Krish

------------------------------------------------------------------------
r106 | (no author) | 2013-12-14 13:09:20 +0530 (Sat, 14 Dec 2013) | 1 line
Merged via: r125, r124, r121

X-T plot and tcon module now uses Preferences settings. -- Krish
------------------------------------------------------------------------
r104 | (no author) | 2013-12-13 19:13:09 +0530 (Fri, 13 Dec 2013) | 4 lines
Merged via: r125

** Last revision has been tested with hardware. Minor modifications added.

-- Krish

------------------------------------------------------------------------
r103 | (no author) | 2013-12-13 14:01:13 +0530 (Fri, 13 Dec 2013) | 8 lines
Merged via: r125

** Res4 modules now uses Preferences to store log and data files.

** Only the latest log file is stored with name 'last_run.log'. The complete data is stored in dictionary files at the end of the run. In case, the run terminates abruptly, the lastest data is atleast available for recovery.

** The data file name is formatted as YYYYMMDD_HHMMSS.xprt or xpiv depedning on the run mode.

-- Krish

