r61 | (no author) | 2013-09-02 13:28:55 +0530 (Mon, 02 Sep 2013) | 1 line

ChangeLog updated. -- Krish
------------------------------------------------------------------------
r60 | (no author) | 2013-09-02 13:28:28 +0530 (Mon, 02 Sep 2013) | 4 lines

** Callback of "Final Temperature" entry box has been disabled. The final temperature is communicated only when the ramp rate is set. This is an artifact of dual slope ramping, where the checking of whether temperature setpoint has crossed the final temperature, is dependant on the sign of ramp rate.

-- Krish

------------------------------------------------------------------------
r59 | (no author) | 2013-08-31 18:38:26 +0530 (Sat, 31 Aug 2013) | 1 line

ChangeLog updated. -- Krish
------------------------------------------------------------------------
r58 | (no author) | 2013-08-31 18:38:08 +0530 (Sat, 31 Aug 2013) | 1 line

Negative temperature ramp rate can be set. -- Krish.
------------------------------------------------------------------------
r57 | (no author) | 2013-08-30 20:40:28 +0530 (Fri, 30 Aug 2013) | 1 line

ChangeLog updated. -- Krish.
------------------------------------------------------------------------
r56 | (no author) | 2013-08-30 20:40:08 +0530 (Fri, 30 Aug 2013) | 18 lines

** While opening lock-in amplifier control interface, the hardware is put in a default known state. The default settings are:

	** Reference amplitude      : 1 V
	** Reference freqquency     : 180 Hz
	** Reference phase          : 0 deg.
	** AC coupling              : OFF
	** Pre-amp gain             : 10
	** Post-amp gain            : 10
	** Integrator time constant : 1 sec.

** Phase values, at some places, have been wrongly twice converted to degree from radian. These have been corrected.

** bCheckTimeout function in xlia.py has been renamed to comm_timedout. This is less ambiguous from the point of view of boolean return type. (bCheckTimeout() == True) is ambiguous, while (comm_timedout() == True) means the communication has timed out.

** Integrator time constants have been changed to 2 ms, 5 ms, and 1 sec. in app_xlia.py.

-- Krish

------------------------------------------------------------------------
r55 | (no author) | 2013-08-29 19:22:44 +0530 (Thu, 29 Aug 2013) | 1 line

ChangeLog updated. -- Krish.
------------------------------------------------------------------------
r54 | (no author) | 2013-08-29 19:22:01 +0530 (Thu, 29 Aug 2013) | 14 lines

** Thermocouple amplifier gain resistor has been changed to 120 ohm (from 27 ohm) and ADC full-scale voltage of thermocouple channel has been changed to 1024 mV. File tcon.py has been updated accordingly.

** Function ascii2xprt in fileie.py has been updated. New features are:
	-- It skips first six lines of the ascii log file in order to read the header.
	-- It returns the filename of the newly created xprt file, which is necessary while importing the file in open menu.

** Voltmeter ranges in res4.py and app_res4.py have been updated. Currently three ranges, viz. 100mV, 1V, and 10V, have been made visible to the user.

** File analyzer.py has been updated to directly display imported runs (previously import used to create xprt file in the background).

** It is worth mentioning that most of the modified lines in 'svn diff' are due to removal of trailing spaces.

-- Krish

------------------------------------------------------------------------
